|YK0#|YKB Roles|000

|GK0How a guild or class fulfills its theme and story can be thought of as a
role. Different guilds and classes can share roles, so their adventuring tools
may overlap without changing what they fundamentally are.|000

|GK0Roles describe capabilities. Guilds remain learned skills and traditions;
classes remain innate parts of a character.|000

|YK0##|YKB Bruiser|000

|GK0Typically melee-based damage dealers, bruisers have a mix of self|000
|GK0preservation and enhancement abilities - typically directly impacting|000
|GK0how they fight. Their direct damage abilities are not usually efficient.|000

|YK0##|YKB Healer|000

|GK0Healers excel at... healing. They usually have ways to heal themselves or
others, can prevent damage, and might have increased regeneration.
Resurrection abilities are generally limited to healer toolkits.|000

|YK0##|YKB Nuker|000

|GK0Nuker toolkits generally have good or great resource efficiency with
powerful damage abilities.|000

|YK0##|YKB Specialist|000

|GK0Rather than direct effects, specialists manipulate themselves, allies,
enemies, or the environment for a benefit. Information-gathering toolkits
typically fall into the specialist role.|000

|YK0##|YKB Tank|000

|GK0Tank toolkits excel at taking damage. They can generally handle the threat
of relatively higher-level creatures, are often found in the toughest armour,
and generally have high health pools.|000

